The real_corpus benchmark's no-regression gate reads perf-baseline.json by op name, requiring each gated op to have an entry whose median_ms and noise_floor_ms are f64; an absent key silently skips the regression rule for that op while a malformed entry panics, so the JSON's keys and per-op field shape must match the op names and Baseline parse the bench uses.
